    This [animated image](/Animation) provides a dynamic and insightful visualization of the [U.S. states by date of statehood](/List_of_U.S._states_by_date_of_statehood), meticulously illustrating the chronological order in which each individual [U.S. state](/U.S._state) formally joined the [Union](/United_States). While the original 13 states can, with historical accuracy, be considered members of the [United States](/United_States) from the pivotal date of the [Declaration of Independence](/United_States_Declaration_of_Independence), for the purposes of this visualization, they are presented as being "admitted" on the specific date each ratified the present [United States Constitution](/United_States_Constitution), marking their formal entry into the new federal structure. It is important to note that this animated sequence deliberately does not address the complex and contentious period of the secession of states that ultimately led to the formation of the [Confederacy](/Confederate_States_of_America). Instead, it focuses solely on the continuous process of admission to the Union, offering a clear, if simplified, representation of the nation's territorial and political evolution.

