*   #### Image 14

    [Yellowstone National Park](/Yellowstone_National_Park)
    Photo credit: Daniel Mayer

    [Yellowstone National Park](/Yellowstone_National_Park) is an iconic [United States National Park](/List_of_U.S._national_parks) that majestically spans across portions of three distinct [states](/U.S._states): [Idaho](/Idaho), [Montana](/Montana), and [Wyoming](/Wyoming). Beyond its geographical spread, Yellowstone holds a singular and historically significant distinction: it is recognized as the first and, indeed, the oldest [national park](/National_park) in the entire world. This groundbreaking designation in 1872 set a global precedent for wilderness preservation. The park is justly famous for its extraordinary [geothermal features](/Geothermal_areas_of_Yellowstone), a mesmerizing landscape of geysers, hot springs, mudpots, and fumaroles, all driven by a massive, active supervolcano beneath its surface. Beyond its geological wonders, Yellowstone is also a vital sanctuary for an array of magnificent wildlife, serving as home to thriving populations of [grizzly bears](/Brown_bear), elusive [wolves](/Wolf), majestic [bison](/American_bison), and graceful [elk](/Wapiti). It stands as a testament to the enduring power and beauty of untouched wilderness, a living laboratory for both ecological and geological processes.

