*   ### More did you know? -
    *   show different entries

    More nuggets of information, some more baffling than others, to fill the void.

*   ...that the [Pewee Valley Confederate Memorial](/Pewee_Valley_Confederate_Cemetery) (pictured) holds the distinction of being the only [American Civil War](/American_Civil_War) [obelisk](/Obelisk) monument in [Kentucky](/Kentucky) to be crafted from [zinc](/Zinc)? A rather specific, and perhaps economical, choice of material for a monument to a lost cause.
*   ...that the [second subtitle](/USA_PATRIOT_Act,_Title_III,_Subtitle_B) of [title III](/USA_PATRIOT_Act,_Title_III) of the [USA PATRIOT Act](/USA_PATRIOT_Act) was largely designed to modify the [Bank Secrecy Act](/Bank_Secrecy_Act), in a concerted effort to make it significantly harder for [money launderers](/Money_launderer) to operate, and concurrently, to make it easier for [law enforcement](/Law_enforcement_agency) and regulatory agencies to effectively police money laundering operations? A bureaucratic attempt to stem the tide of illicit finance, no doubt proving as effective as most such endeavors.
*   ...that [Senator](/United_States_Senate) [William A. Blakley](/William_A._Blakley) of the [U.S. state](/U.S._state) of [Texas](/Texas), in his younger days, worked as a humble [ranch](/Ranch) hand? A rather grounding origin story for a figure who would later navigate the lofty halls of the Senate.

